Barn: Marie Louise f. 22. — Stud:ex. i Sthlm 09, med. kand. v. Karol. inst. 13 o. med. lic. där 19. Utr. stud:res. samt kongressdelt. nästan årl. 21-38. Und:läk. v. Maria sjukh. med. avd. 15, v. epid:’sjukh. i Sthlm 19, v. Söderby sjukh. två mån. s. å., e. läk. v. Kronpr. Lovisas vårdans t. 19-20, und :läk. v. Sachsska barnsjukh. 20, aman. v. Karol. inst. pediatr. klinik 20-21, und :läk. v. barnsjukh. Samariten 21, bitr. läk. v. Gbgs barnsjukh. med. avd. 22-24, stadsdi-str:läk. i Gbg :sed. 24, läk. v. Gbgs stads upptagn:hem f. barn v. Vidkärr m. fi. barnhem, v. Majornas sjukh. 24-25, järnv :läk. v. SJ sex mån. 25. Fält-läk :stip. i Fik res. 16-19, bat:läk. v. Fik 19-24, i dess res. 24. translated: Johannsen, Nicolai Josef, urban district doctor, Gothenburg, b. 7/10/91 in Stockholm to merchant Nicolai J. and Marie Adam. M. 21 with Anna Lisa Wennersten. Children: Marie Louise b. 22. - Secondary school in Stockholm 09, medical candidate at Karolinska Institute 13, and medical licentiate there in 19. Foreign study trips and participation in congresses almost annually from 21 to 38. Assistant doctor at Maria Hospital medical department 15, at the epidemic hospital in Stockholm in 19, at Söderby Hospital for two months the same year, employed doctor at Crown Princess Lovisa's care institute from 19-20, assistant doctor at Sachs Children's Hospital 20, trainee at Karolinska Institute pediatric clinic 20-21, assistant doctor at Samaritans Children's Hospital 21, assistant doctor at Gothenburg's Children's Hospital medical department 22-24, urban district doctor in Gothenburg since 24, doctor at Gothenburg's Municipal Children's Homes in Vidkärr and other orphanages, at Majorna Hospital 24-25, railway doctor at SJ for six months in 25. Field medical scholarship in the Finnish Army reserves 16-19, battalion doctor in the Finnish Army 19-24, in its reserves from 24. Chairman of the Gothenburg School Vacation Colony Association since 32 and on the board of the Broström Children's Hospital since 43. Has written about 30 papers on pediatric and internal medicine. Hobbies: sailing, agriculture.
